---
import Base from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';import EmailCTA from '../components/EmailCTA.astro';import {products} from '../data/products';import {applications} from '../data/applications';import {site} from '../config/site';
const schema=[{'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'Organization',name:'INNO',url:site.siteUrl,email:site.email,logo:new URL('/images/logo/inno-logo.png',site.siteUrl).toString(),description:site.description},{'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'WebSite',name:site.name,url:site.siteUrl,inLanguage:'en'}];
---
<Base title="Transformer Oil & Winding Temperature Indicators" description="INNO supplies transformer oil temperature indicators, winding temperature indicators and monitoring devices for oil-immersed transformer projects worldwide." schema={schema} image="/images/scenes/transformer-substation-hero.png">
  <section class="hero"><img class="hero-scene" src="/images/scenes/transformer-substation-hero.png" alt="Oil-immersed power transformer in a high-voltage substation" width="1792" height="1024"><div class="hero-shade"></div><div class="container hero-grid"><div class="hero-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Oil-immersed transformer instruments</p><h1>Transformer temperature, clearly controlled.</h1><p>Specify oil and winding temperature indicators for local reading, cooling control, alarm, trip and remote monitoring.</p><div class="actions"><a class="button" href="/products/">Compare products</a><a class="text-link" href={`mailto:${site.email}?subject=Transformer%20temperature%20product%20inquiry`}>Email INNO</a></div></div><div class="hero-panel"><img src="/images/products/bwr2-winding-temperature-indicator.webp" alt="INNO BWR2 winding temperature indicator for oil-immersed transformers" width="800" height="800"><strong>Selection starts with the measured value</strong><dl><div><dt>Top-oil temperature</dt><dd>OTI</dd></div><div><dt>Simulated winding temperature</dt><dd>WTI</dd></div><div><dt>Temperature, level and pressure</dt><dd>RS485</dd></div></dl></div></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="section-head"><h2>One focused transformer instrument range</h2><p class="lead">INNO organizes the range around the actual thermal value and control task, not a generic list of electrical accessories.</p></div><div class="grid two"><article class="card metric"><h3>Oil temperature indicators</h3><p>BWY and BWY2 instruments indicate transformer top-oil temperature and provide contacts for cooling and alarm functions.</p><a class="arrow" href="/products/transformer-oil-temperature-indicators/">Compare oil indicators</a></article><article class="card metric"><h3>Winding temperature indicators</h3><p>BWR and BWR2 systems combine top-oil temperature with a load-related thermal rise to indicate simulated winding temperature.</p><a class="arrow" href="/products/transformer-winding-temperature-indicators/">Compare winding indicators</a></article><article class="card metric"><h3>Integrated monitoring devices</h3><p>Powered field devices acquire oil temperature with oil level and pressure for a compatible remote terminal.</p><a class="arrow" href="/products/transformer-temperature-monitoring-devices/">Review monitoring devices</a></article><article class="card metric"><h3>Replacement and customization</h3><p>Match model code, scale, contacts, signal, capillary, bulb, thread and mounting before approving a replacement.</p><a class="arrow" href="/oem-customization/">Review selection inputs</a></article></div></div></section>
  <section class="section tint"><div class="container"><div class="section-head"><h2>Real products with referenced technical data</h2><p class="lead">Each page separates confirmed planning values from configuration details that still require a current datasheet and drawing.</p></div><div class="grid">{products.slice(0,4).map(product=><article class="card"><a href={`/products/${product.slug}/`}><img src={product.image} alt={`${product.model} transformer temperature indicator product`} width="800" height="800" loading="lazy"></a><p class="eyebrow">{product.model}</p><h3><a href={`/products/${product.slug}/`}>{product.name}</a></h3><p>{product.summary}</p><a class="arrow" href={`/products/${product.slug}/`}>Review specifications</a></article>)}</div></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container prose"><h2>What is transformer temperature monitoring?</h2><div class="answer-block">Transformer temperature monitoring is the coordinated indication, control and remote acquisition of thermal values that describe oil-immersed transformer operation. An oil temperature indicator measures top oil. A winding temperature indicator simulates winding temperature from top-oil temperature and load current. Powered monitoring devices can send additional values to a remote system.</div><p>The distinction matters because each value supports a different engineering interpretation. Top-oil temperature shows the condition of the cooling medium near the sensing point. Simulated winding temperature adds a calibrated thermal rise to represent load effect. Direct embedded winding hot-spot measurement uses another measurement architecture and should not be described as the same function.</p><p>A complete project also defines what happens after measurement. Adjustable contacts can start fans or pumps, issue a high-temperature alarm or contribute to trip logic. Pt100, 4-20 mA and RS485 interfaces can carry values to a panel or supervisory system. Selection therefore includes both the field instrument and the receiving control chain.</p></div></section>
  <section class="section tint"><div class="container scene-layout"><div><img class="scene-image" src="/images/scenes/transformer-temperature-inspection.png" alt="Electrical engineer inspecting a transformer temperature instrument in a substation" width="1536" height="1024" loading="lazy"></div><div><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Field applications</p><h2>Engineering paths for new and existing transformers</h2></div><div class="application-list">{applications.slice(0,4).map((item,index)=><article><span>0{index+1}</span><div><h3><a href={`/applications/${item.slug}/`}>{item.title}</a></h3><p>{item.intro}</p><a class="arrow" href={`/applications/${item.slug}/`}>Plan the application</a></div></article>)}</div></div></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container grid two"><div class="prose"><h2>Prepare a useful product inquiry</h2><p>A model recommendation is more reliable when the email includes the transformer type, existing model, measuring range, contact functions, signal, power supply, capillary, bulb and thread, mounting interface, quantity and destination. Attach a nameplate photograph or drawing for replacement work.</p><a class="button" href="/contact/">View the email checklist</a></div><div class="card"><h3>Common signal options</h3><p><strong>Pt100:</strong> a resistance signal that requires a compatible receiving input.</p><p><strong>4-20 mA:</strong> a conditioned current loop with a defined temperature scale.</p><p><strong>RS485:</strong> digital communication that requires an agreed protocol, address and register map.</p></div></div></section>
  <EmailCTA subject="INNO transformer temperature instrument inquiry" />
</Base>
